            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>üìö What is a Database?</h2>
                
                <div class="analogy-box">
                    <h3>üóÉÔ∏è Think of a Database Like a Digital Filing Cabinet</h3>
                    
                    <canvas id="filingCabinetCanvas" width="600" height="300"></canvas>
                    <script>
                        const ctx = document.getElementById('filingCabinetCanvas').getContext('2d');
                        
                        // Draw filing cabinet
                        ctx.fillStyle = '#6b7280';
                        ctx.fillRect(100, 50, 150, 200);
                        
                        // Draw drawers
                        const drawers = ['Customers', 'Products', 'Orders', 'Invoices'];
                        drawers.forEach((label, i) => {
                            const y = 70 + (i * 45);
                            ctx.fillStyle = '#e5e7eb';
                            ctx.fillRect(110, y, 130, 35);
                            ctx.fillStyle = '#374151';
                            ctx.fillRect(165, y + 12, 20, 10);
                            
                            ctx.fillStyle = '#1f2937';
                            ctx.font = '12px Arial';
                            ctx.fillText(label, 115, y + 22);
                        });
                        
                        // Draw arrow
                        ctx.strokeStyle = '#667eea';
                        ctx.lineWidth = 2;
                        ctx.beginPath();
                        ctx.moveTo(270, 150);
                        ctx.lineTo(320, 150);
                        ctx.stroke();
                        
                        // Draw database icon
                        ctx.fillStyle = '#667eea';
                        ctx.beginPath();
                        ctx.ellipse(400, 100, 60, 20, 0, 0, Math.PI * 2);
                        ctx.fill();
                        ctx.fillRect(340, 100, 120, 80);
                        ctx.beginPath();
                        ctx.ellipse(400, 180, 60, 20, 0, 0, Math.PI * 2);
                        ctx.fill();
                        
                        // Labels
                        ctx.fillStyle = '#1f2937';
                        ctx.font = '14px Arial';
                        ctx.fillText('Traditional Filing', 120, 30);
                        ctx.fillText('Database System', 360, 30);
                        
                        ctx.font = '12px Arial';
                        ctx.fillText('Manual', 140, 270);
                        ctx.fillText('Slow', 150, 285);
                        ctx.fillText('Automated', 370, 270);
                        ctx.fillText('Lightning Fast', 360, 285);
                    </script>
                    
                    <p>A <strong>database</strong> is an organized collection of data that can be easily accessed, managed, and updated. Just like a filing cabinet organizes papers into folders, a database organizes information into structured formats.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="concept-card">
                    <h3>Why Do We Need Databases?</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>üìä <strong>Organization:</strong> Keep data structured and easy to find</li>
                        <li>‚ö° <strong>Speed:</strong> Retrieve information in milliseconds</li>
                        <li>üîí <strong>Security:</strong> Control who can see and modify data</li>
                        <li>üîÑ <strong>Consistency:</strong> Ensure data follows rules and stays accurate</li>
                        <li>üë• <strong>Multi-user:</strong> Many people can access data simultaneously</li>
                        <li>üíæ <strong>Backup:</strong> Protect against data loss</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>üî§ Essential Database Terminology</h2>
                
                <div class="term-grid">
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <div class="term-icon">üóÑÔ∏è</div>
                        <div class="term-title">Database</div>
                        <p>A container that holds all your data tables and relationships. Like a warehouse for information.</p>
                        <code>Example: wordpress_db</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <div class="term-icon">üìã</div>
                        <div class="term-title">Table</div>
                        <p>A collection of related data organized in rows and columns, like a spreadsheet.</p>
                        <code>Example: users, products</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <div class="term-icon">üìù</div>
                        <div class="term-title">Record/Row</div>
                        <p>A single entry in a table containing all information about one item.</p>
                        <code>Example: One customer's data</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <div class="term-icon">üìä</div>
                        <div class="term-title">Field/Column</div>
                        <p>A specific piece of information in a table, like name or email.</p>
                        <code>Example: first_name, price</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <div class="term-icon">üîë</div>
                        <div class="term-title">Primary Key</div>
                        <p>A unique identifier for each record, ensuring no duplicates.</p>
                        <code>Example: user_id, product_id</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <div class="term-icon">üîó</div>
                        <div class="term-title">Foreign Key</div>
                        <p>Links one table to another, creating relationships between data.</p>
                        <code>Example: customer_id in orders</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <div class="term-icon">üèÉ</div>
                        <div class="term-title">Query</div>
                        <p>A request for data from the database, like asking a question.</p>
                        <code>SELECT * FROM users</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <div class="term-icon">üìë</div>
                        <div class="term-title">Index</div>
                        <p>A data structure that speeds up searches, like a book's index.</p>
                        <code>INDEX on email column</code>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>üèóÔ∏è Database Structure Visualization</h2>
                
                <canvas id="structureCanvas" width="600" height="400"></canvas>
                <script>
                    const sctx = document.getElementById('structureCanvas').getContext('2d');
                    
                    // Draw database container
                    sctx.fillStyle = '#ede9fe';
                    sctx.fillRect(50, 50, 500, 320);
                    sctx.fillStyle = '#8b5cf6';
                    sctx.fillRect(50, 50, 500, 40);
                    sctx.fillStyle = 'white';
                    sctx.font = 'bold 18px Arial';
                    sctx.fillText('DATABASE: online_store', 200, 75);
                    
                    // Draw table
                    sctx.fillStyle = '#f3f4f6';
                    sctx.fillRect(100, 120, 400, 200);
                    sctx.fillStyle = '#667eea';
                    sctx.fillRect(100, 120, 400, 35);
                    sctx.fillStyle = 'white';
                    sctx.font = 'bold 14px Arial';
                    sctx.fillText('TABLE: customers', 250, 142);
                    
                    // Draw column headers
                    const columns = ['id', 'name', 'email', 'phone', 'city'];
                    sctx.fillStyle = '#e5e7eb';
                    sctx.fillRect(100, 155, 400, 30);
                    sctx.fillStyle = '#374151';
                    sctx.font = 'bold 11px Arial';
                    columns.forEach((col, i) => {
                        sctx.fillText(col, 110 + (i * 80), 175);
                    });
                    
                    // Draw rows
                    const rows = [
                        ['1', 'John Doe', 'john@email', '555-0001', 'New York'],
                        ['2', 'Jane Smith', 'jane@email', '555-0002', 'Los Angeles'],
                        ['3', 'Bob Johnson', 'bob@email', '555-0003', 'Chicago']
                    ];
                    
                    rows.forEach((row, rowIndex) => {
                        const y = 185 + (rowIndex * 30);
                        sctx.fillStyle = rowIndex % 2 === 0 ? 'white' : '#f9fafb';
                        sctx.fillRect(100, y, 400, 30);
                        
                        sctx.fillStyle = '#6b7280';
                        sctx.font = '10px Arial';
                        row.forEach((cell, colIndex) => {
                            sctx.fillText(cell, 110 + (colIndex * 80), y + 20);
                        });
                    });
                    
                    // Draw primary key indicator
                    sctx.strokeStyle = '#f59e0b';
                    sctx.lineWidth = 2;
                    sctx.strokeRect(105, 160, 70, 125);
                    sctx.fillStyle = '#f59e0b';
                    sctx.font = '10px Arial';
                    sctx.fillText('Primary Key', 105, 300);
                    
                    // Labels
                    sctx.fillStyle = '#1f2937';
                    sctx.font = '12px Arial';
                    sctx.fillText('Fields/Columns ‚Üí', 510, 170);
                    sctx.fillText('‚Üì', 75, 200);
                    sctx.fillText('Records', 40, 230);
                    sctx.fillText('/Rows', 45, 245);
                </script>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>üñ•Ô∏è Database Management System (DBMS)</h2>
                
                <div class="concept-card">
                    <h3>What is a DBMS?</h3>
                    <p>A <strong>Database Management System</strong> is software that acts as an intermediary between users and the database. Think of it as the librarian who helps you find and manage books!</p>
                    
                    <div class="mermaid">
                        graph LR
                            A[User/Application] -->|SQL Commands| B[DBMS]
                            B -->|Manages| C[Database]
                            C -->|Returns Data| B
                            B -->|Results| A
                            
                            style B fill:#667eea,color:white
                    </div>
                    
                    <h4>Popular DBMS Examples:</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>üê¨ <strong>MySQL</strong> - Open source, used by WordPress</li>
                        <li>üêò <strong>PostgreSQL</strong> - Advanced open source</li>
                        <li>üè¢ <strong>Oracle</strong> - Enterprise solution</li>
                        <li>ü™ü <strong>Microsoft SQL Server</strong> - Windows ecosystem</li>
                        <li>üçÉ <strong>MongoDB</strong> - NoSQL database</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>üîÑ CRUD Operations</h2>
                
                <p>The four fundamental operations you can perform on data:</p>
                
                <div class="term-grid">
                    <div class="term-card" style="border-color: #10b981;">
                        <div class="term-icon">‚ûï</div>
                        <div class="term-title" style="color: #10b981;">CREATE</div>
                        <p>Add new data to the database</p>
                        <code>INSERT INTO users...</code>
                        <p><em>Example: Adding a new customer</em></p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card" style="border-color: #0891b2;">
                        <div class="term-icon">üìñ</div>
                        <div class="term-title" style="color: #0891b2;">READ</div>
                        <p>Retrieve data from the database</p>
                        <code>SELECT * FROM users...</code>
                        <p><em>Example: Viewing customer list</em></p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card" style="border-color: #f59e0b;">
                        <div class="term-icon">‚úèÔ∏è</div>
                        <div class="term-title" style="color: #f59e0b;">UPDATE</div>
                        <p>Modify existing data</p>
                        <code>UPDATE users SET...</code>
                        <p><em>Example: Changing an address</em></p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card" style="border-color: #ef4444;">
                        <div class="term-icon">üóëÔ∏è</div>
                        <div class="term-title" style="color: #ef4444;">DELETE</div>
                        <p>Remove data from the database</p>
                        <code>DELETE FROM users...</code>
                        <p><em>Example: Removing old records</em></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

